<title type="html"><![CDATA[Max ERPOM access delay?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2911&amp;p=21672#p21672"><![CDATA[
If I remember right, for NTSC, the PRG /CS line is active for 6 master cycles (at 21.477272 MHz), or about 279 ns.  The CHR /RD line (during screen rendering) is active for four master cycles, or about 186 ns.  PAL timing is slower, so if it works for NTSC it'll also work for PAL.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=360">dvdmth</a> — Mon Jan 29, 2007 11:17 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
