<title type="html"><![CDATA[Max ERPOM access delay?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2911&amp;p=21670#p21670"><![CDATA[
Well, for PRGROM about anything will do (to be exact you have to mesure the high time of M2, and that is the exact maximum acess time allowed), and you'd need to be more carefull with CHRROM, because the processor is 3 times slower (I guess 120ns or less EPROMs are okay, like SNES' Fastrom games). Again, the only real answer is to take an oscilloscope and measure the low time of CHR /RD.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Mon Jan 29, 2007 9:16 am</p><hr />
